HEADWORD: Egotistical
<hw>E`go*tis"tic*al</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <def>Addicted to, or manifesting,
egotism; having an exaggerated view of one's own importance or good
qualities.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> egotistic; narcissistic; self-loving; conceited;
vain; self-important; opinionated.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Egotistically</ent>⟦br⟧
